Donâ€™t put your umbrellas away just yet. The latest forecast from the South African Weather Service (SAWS) shows that more rainy conditions are expected in KwaZulu-Natal for the rest of the week. Thandiwe Gumede, a weather forecaster, said there is no weather alert issued for Tuesday in KZN but there is a 60% chance for showers in the province. She said there is also a 60% chance of showers and thundershowers expected on Wednesday and Thursday. Gumede said residents in the eastern parts of the province will only start experiencing warmer conditions on Friday but those in the southern Drakensberg areas should expect conditions to remain cooler and wet for the rest of the week. She said there was a significant amount of rainfall in the province on Monday, with 33 millilitres recorded in Pietermaritzburg. 